# Protected paths — the kernel of the self-building organism.
#
# This is the single definition. Every enforcer reads THIS file; none carries
# its own copy, and GUARDRAILS.md describes the control rather than restating
# the paths, because a second copy is a second source of truth and will drift.
#
# What enforces it:
#
#   1. The Stem refuses to merge a Terrarium commit that touches any path
#      listed here, so a Sprout cannot rewrite the orchestrator that is
#      running it. Enforced by the trusted side — a Sprout is not asked to
#      cooperate.
#   2. Code-owner review is required before such a change can land on the
#      default branch, so every author is caught regardless of the route the
#      edit took.
#
# Editing a listed path is normal and expected. What is not possible is
# landing that edit without a human control-plane review.
#
# Syntax:
#
#   * one pattern per line; blank lines and lines beginning with # are ignored
#   * a pattern ending in "/" matches every path beneath that directory
#   * any other pattern is matched against the whole path, with the shell
#     wildcards * ? and [] available
#
# A malformed pattern is an error rather than a line to skip: a control that
# silently ignores the part of itself it cannot parse is not a control.

# The list itself. Removing or narrowing it is a change to a protected path,
# which is what stops the guard being disabled in passing.
.github/protected-paths

# Continuous integration: the Adaptive Immune System, and the enforcement
# surface for everything else here.
.github/workflows/
.github/CODEOWNERS
.github/dependabot.yml

# Stem kernel: the entry point and the daemon bootstrap. A Sprout editing
# these can corrupt the process currently executing it.
cmd/stem/main.go
cmd/stem/cmdserve.go

# The governed capability registry and its boundary/parity tests — where
# delegation decides what a Pollen may do.
cmd/stem/internal/core/

# Enforcement code itself. The guard must not be editable by the thing it
# guards.
cmd/stem/internal/conductor/protectedpaths.go
scripts/

# Governance. These define the rules the rest of the work is judged against.
AGENTS.md
GUARDRAILS.md
ARCHITECTURE.md
SYNTHETIC-TAXONOMY.md
CAPABILITIES.md
USE-CASES.md

# Environment secrets.
.env
